### Steps to reproduce
When there is more than one listener for each event in "_evnets", the off method can delete the event listener. When each event in "_events" listens, only one listener can't remove the event.

``` javascript
// one event listener

var Bus = require('vue');
Bus.$on('eat', func);
console.log(Bus._events); // {"eat": [ func ]}
Bus.$off("eat"); 
console.log(Bus._events); //{"eat": [ func ]}

// two event listener or  more

var Bus = require('vue');
Bus.$on('eat', func);
Bus.$on('sleep', func1)
console.log(Bus._events); // log --- {"eat": [ func ], "sleep": [ func1 ]}
Bus.$off("eat"); 
console.log(Bus._events); // log --- {"eat": null, sleep: [ func1 ]}
```

### What is expected?
Listener cannot be removed

### What is actually happening?
When using the "off" method, the corresponding listener can be removed， And remove the key of the _events object

